<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 8:09PM CDT  by NWS Lubbock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Childress, northeastern Motley, Hall and southeastern Briscoe
Counties through 900 PM CDT...
At 809 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Turkey, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Turkey, Northfield, Estelline and Plaska Community.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
